These List of Focus types I stole from Castersrealm:<br>
<br>
<br>
Reagent Conservation - Percent chance to not use a component on spells. <br>
Extended Enhancement - Percent increase on duration of buffs. <br>
Improved Damage - Percent increase on Direct Damage spells. <br>
Spell Haste - Percent reduction on casting time of dd's, heal's. <br>
Mana Preservation - Percent reduction in mana cost of dd's, heal's. <br>
Improved Healing - Percent increase in amount healed. <br>
Extended Range - Percent increase in spell range to target. <br>
Summoning Haste - Percent reduction in time of summoned objects (non-undead pets only). <br>
Summoning Efficiency - Percent reduction in mana cost of summoned items (non-undead pets only). <br>
Enhancement Haste - Percent reduction in casting of buff spells. <br>
Affliction Efficiency - Percent reduction in mana cost of dots. <br>
Extended Affliction - Percent increase in duration of dot's, more ticks, same damage per tick as prior, more total damage. <br>
Reanimation Haste - Percent reduction time in casting undead pets (undead pets only). <br>
Reanimation Efficiency - Percent reduction in mana cost of undead pets (undead pets only).<br>
